<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><hymn_number>275</hymn_number>
<author>Stefania Piovesan</author>
<title>Deep down</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 What is what I see? Where is where
 I've been now? Where is the place
 Where everyone's got names
 Never heard before?
 I have seen the poorness of a queen, golden evil
 I have dreamed about a man
 Who walks on the water

[V2]
 It feels like nobody
 Sees you when you're crying so
 Deep down deep down
 Tears makes you blind but
 Jesus is the light you have
 Deep down deep down

[V3]
 What is what I see? Where is where
 I'll go now? Where is the place
 Where everyone's got names
 Never heard before?
 I have seen the sadness of a queen,
 She needs to get ahead
 I have dreamed about a man
 Who walks on the water

[V4]
 It feels like nobody
 Sees you when you're crying so
 Deep down deep down
 Tears makes you blind but
 Jesus is the light you have
 Deep down deep down</lyrics>
</song>